SIMPLE: epigene
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Epigene
<hw>Ep"i*gene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>epi-</ets> + Gr. <grk>gi`gnesqai</grk> to be born, grow.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>Foreign; unnatural; unusual;
-- said of forms of crystals not natural to the substances in which they
are found.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Formed originating on the surface
of the earth; -- opposed to <contr>hypogene</contr>; <as>as,
<ex>epigene</ex> rocks</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epigenesis</ent>⟦br⟧
